ltations are not intended for clinical counseling.  If you are experiencing a crisis or emergency and require services outside of business hours please call 911.  The Wellness Center is not a walk-in clinic, if you have a physical medical concern, we recommend contacting your primary care physician.  If you are attempting to seek on-going counseling for depression, anxiety or any other concern, please contact the UIC Counseling Center .  The UIC Counseling Center is confidential and free to all registered UIC students. Click the link below for information on the Counseling Center.  All University employees, except staff in the Campus Advocacy Network (CAN) and the Counseling Center who provide advocacy or counseling services, have a duty to report any incidents involving sexual misconduct. Refer to a description of Responsible Employee. For more information visit: https://sexualmisconduct.uic.edu/policy/campus-roles-responsibilities/  Unless otherwise informed by a Wellness Center staff member, you will hear back from Wellness Center staff within 48-72 hours of your initial request. Please note that due to unpredictable events appointments might need to be rescheduled.          Instructions      UIC Counseling Center Information and Emergency Support Services        Individual Wellness Consultation    Disclaimer * Required  I Understand I have read the above information about individual consultations and the other resources before submitting this form. I understand that my request is for a Health and Wellness concern only and that I am requesting to meet with a health educator for a one-time meeting. Wellness Consultation Form * Required College Transition Home Sickness Making a Friend Nutrition Guidance (As a Lifestyle) Report a Rape (*Wellness Center Staff are Mandatory Reporters) Responsible Drinking Request Access to Food Request Help to Access Housing Safe Sex Sleep Deprevation Smoking Cessation Stress Managment Street Safety Study Skills First and Last Name * 